# Tests for New Features and Components

When adding or changing behavior in this project, add or update tests in the same change. Do not ship new features or UI without meaningful coverage.

## When to add tests

| Change | Test approach |
|--------|---------------|
| New React component | Colocated `*.test.tsx` with React Testing Library |
| Pure logic (utils, schemas, metrics) | Colocated `*.test.ts` unit tests |
| Server actions / auth | Colocated tests with `vi.mock` for DB, Clerk, `next/cache` |
| Bug fix | Regression test that fails without the fix |

Skip tests only for trivial, non-behavioral changes (copy, styling-only tweaks with no logic).

## Conventions

- **Colocate** — place `foo.test.ts` or `foo.test.tsx` next to `foo.ts` / `foo.tsx`.
- **Fixtures** — reuse shared data from `src/test/factories.ts`.
- **Extract logic** — keep complex logic in `src/lib/` modules so it can be unit tested directly.
- **Run locally** — `npm run test:run` before finishing (CI runs tests on push).

## Examples

```tsx
// ✅ Component test — src/components/banking/summary-cards.test.tsx
import { render, screen } from "@testing-library/react";
import { SummaryCards } from "./summary-cards";

it("formats balances as currency", () => {
  render(<SummaryCards checkingBalance="12450.80" /* ... */ />);
  expect(screen.getByText("$12,450.80")).toBeInTheDocument();
});
```

```ts
// ✅ Logic test — src/lib/banking/transfer-schema.test.ts
import { describe, it, expect } from "vitest";
import { transferSchema } from "./transfer-schema";

it("rejects amounts over the daily limit", () => {
  expect(transferSchema.safeParse({ amount: 99999 }).success).toBe(false);
});
```

Coverage thresholds are enforced in `vitest.config.ts` — new code should not lower overall coverage.
